The paper discusses a novel algorithm for incorporating cost information into deep learning, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computational linguistics (cs.CL). However, since the paper focuses on deep learning and its application to cost-sensitive classification, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.AI and cs.CV. The other two sub-categories, cs.NE and cs.CL, are less likely but still possible depending on the specific application of the proposed algorithm.
